<LP>
   TORONTO -- NHI Nelson Holdings International Ltd. said it
expects to report a gain of about 2.5 million Canadian
dollars (U.S.$2.2 million) in the current quarter from the
repurchase of its 6% convertible subordinated debentures.
   The company said it paid about C$2.5 million to repurchase
C$5 million of the debentures, due Oct. 31. A spokesman said
that the company has about C$8 million of the debentures
still outstanding and that it would be prepared to consider
further discounted repurchases.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   NHI is the holding company for Nelson Entertainment Group.
NHI had net income last year of $4.5 million on revenue of
$108.6 million.
